<commentary id="fs-id1167065943530">
<title>Discussion for (a)</title>
<para id="fs-id1167065030403">This is enough energy to lift a 1-kg ball about 1 m up from the ground. The flash lasts for about 0.001 s, so the power delivered by the capacitor during this brief time is  <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
  <m:mi>P</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac>
